EOTYPED MOVEMENT DISORDER"}, {"i": 617, "t": "F99"}, {"i": 618, "t": "UNSPECIFIED MENTAL DISORDER"}, {"i": 619, "t": "in progress"}, {"i": 620, "t": "ICD-10 CODE NOT ASSIGNED"}, {"i": 621, "t": "SYMPTOM DOMAINS OF PRIMARY PSYCHOTIC DISORDERS"}, {"i": 622, "t": "PREMENSTRUAL DYSPHORIC DISORDER (PMDD)"}, {"i": 623, "t": "PERSONALITY DIFFICULTY"}, {"i": 624, "t": "OBSTRUCTIVE SLEEP APNOEA (OSA)"}, {"i": 625, "t": "NARCOLEPSY"}, {"i": 626, "t": "‹ SCHIZOPHRENIA SPECTRUM"}, {"i": 627, "t": "ICD-11"}, {"i": 628, "t": "6A21"}, {"i": 629, "t": "SCHIZOAFFECTIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 630, "t": "Schizoaffective Disorder"}, {"i": 631, "t": "ICD-10"}, {"i": 632, "t": "F25"}, {"i": 633, "t": "SCHIZOAFFECTIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 634, "t": "DSM-5-TR"}, {"i": 635, "t": "SCHIZOAFFECTIVE DISORDER"}, {"i": 636, "t": "Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 637, "t": "History"}, {"i": 638, "t": "epidemiology"}, {"i": 639, "t": "Aetiology and pathogenesis"}, {"i": 640, "t": "clinical picture"}, {"i": 641, "t": "diagnosis"}, {"i": 642, "t": "Examination and assessment"}, {"i": 643, "t": "treatment"}, {"i": 644, "t": "prognosis"}, {"i": 645, "t": "Myths and misconceptions"}, {"i": 646, "t": "Sources"}, {"i": 647, "t": "1. Definition and nosology"}, {"i": 648, "t": "Schizoaffective disorder (ICD-11:"}, {"i": 649, "t": "6A21"}, {"i": 650, "t": "Schizoaffective Disorder; DSM-5-TR: 295.70) — psychotic symptoms (delusion, hallucination, disorganized speech) and affective episode (manic or depressive) observed together during the same clinical episode, but additionally"}, {"i": 651, "t": "Continuation of psychotic symptoms even outside affective episodes."}, {"i": 652, "t": "ilkin psixotik pozuntudur."}, {"i": 653, "t": "Disorder on spectrum of psychotic disorders"}, {"i": 654, "t": "an intermediate condition between schizophrenia and affective disorder"}, {"i": 655, "t": "On one hand, it is differentiated from \"affective disorder with psychotic features,\" and on the other hand, from \"schizophrenia\" (by the persistence of psychotic symptoms independent of the context of an affective episode)."}, {"i": 656, "t": "DSM-5-TR — two type specifiers:"}, {"i": 657, "t": "bipolyar tip"}, {"i": 658, "t": "(manic and/or depressive episodes) and"}, {"i": 659, "t": "depresiv tip"}, {"i": 660, "t": "(only depressive episodes). In ICD-11, sub-specifications are parallel — according to the type of affective episode."}, {"i": 661, "t": "2. History"}, {"i": 662, "t": "Kasanin J. (1933)"}, {"i": 663, "t": "The term \"acute schizoaffective psychosis\" was first introduced; a rapid onset and favorable prognosis were emphasized."}, {"i": 664, "t": "1970s"}, {"i": 665, "t": "— Carpenter W., Strauss J., Bartko J. — research as a distinct clinical entity from schizophrenia and affective disorder."}, {"i": 666, "t": "DSM-III (1980)"}, {"i": 667, "t": "— Schizoaffective disorder as a \"mixed\" category."}, {"i": 668, "t": "DSM-IV (1994), DSM-5 (2013)"}, {"i": 669, "t": "– diagnostic criteria have been clarified; bipolar/depressive type distinction retained."}, {"i": 670, "t": "ICD-11 (2019)"}, {"i": 671, "t": "Affective episode type sub-specifications."}, {"i": 672, "t": "Diaqnostik validlik debati"}, {"i": 673, "t": "Malhi G.S. et al. Aust N Z J Psychiatry 2008, Lake C.R., Hurwitz N. Curr Psychiatry Rep 2007: whether schizoaffective disorder is a distinct entity separate from schizophrenia and affective disorder is debated; some researchers view it within a spectrum concept."}, {"i": 674, "t": "3. Epidemiology"}, {"i": 675, "t": "Lifetime prevalence:"}, {"i": 676, "t": "0.3% (Perälä J. et al. Arch Gen Psychiatry 2007 Finland population study, n=8000)."}, {"i": 677, "t": "Approximately half the prevalence of schizophrenia (~0.5–0.7%)."}, {"i": 678, "t": "Sex:"}, {"i": 679, "t": "Relatively more frequent in women (1:1.2–1.5); depressive type dominant in women."}]